51
00:03:03,478 --> 00:03:04,458
Give them some context.

52
00:03:05,339 --> 00:03:08,481
Because these absolutely apply, I believe, to the products

53
00:03:08,541 --> 00:03:09,922
that you guys make every day.

54
00:03:10,842 --> 00:03:11,863
So know your audience.

55
00:03:12,818 --> 00:03:13,538
Don't bore them.

56
00:03:13,839 --> 00:03:16,141
Obviously, you want to know who you're making your art for.

57
00:03:16,421 --> 00:03:21,245
You're going to tailor it to things that interest them, to the technologies that they use and

58
00:03:21,325 --> 00:03:25,468
understand, to things that are going to intrigue them, little bits of magic that are going

59
00:03:25,488 --> 00:03:26,289
to make them wonder.

60
00:03:26,930 --> 00:03:28,131
You don't talk down to them.

61
00:03:28,211 --> 00:03:30,873
You don't say, well, this is for kids, so I don't have to try as hard.

62
00:03:31,413 --> 00:03:33,535
You try and make it as great as possible.

63
00:03:34,035 --> 00:03:35,096
Wear your guest's shoes.

64
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:38,761
Anybody who's worked in testing knows this is very important.

65
00:03:39,301 --> 00:03:42,923
You could create the most fabulous attraction,

66
00:03:43,023 --> 00:03:44,944
but it requires you to walk a marathon.

67
00:03:45,284 --> 00:03:46,645
That's not going to be very popular.

68
00:03:47,045 --> 00:03:48,926
You need to understand who your guests are

69
00:03:49,686 --> 00:03:52,227
and really design for them.

70
00:03:53,088 --> 00:03:54,829
Organize the flow of good people and ideas.

71
00:03:54,889 --> 00:03:57,210
This is just basic, good storytelling.

72
00:03:57,230 --> 00:03:58,110
You want to be clear.

73
00:03:58,490 --> 00:04:00,011
You want them to know your intention.

74
00:04:00,171 --> 00:04:02,572
And you want to show them where they're going

75
00:04:02,592 --> 00:04:03,593
and why they're going there.

76
00:04:04,725 --> 00:04:07,126
Now create a weenie. A weenie is Walt's word.

77
00:04:07,927 --> 00:04:13,109
A weenie is a large visual object that draws your focus, that really grounds and sets the

78
00:04:13,149 --> 00:04:18,532
stage for an area. So at Disneyland, the castle is the first weenie that you see when you

79
00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:21,253
enter the park. It draws you. You know you're there.

80
00:04:21,954 --> 00:04:25,695
When you turn right towards Tomorrowland, what do you see?

81
00:04:25,875 --> 00:04:29,397
You see the weenie down there. It's Space Mountain.

82
00:04:30,331 --> 00:04:33,554
So these things give people focus, things to look at.

83
00:04:33,574 --> 00:04:35,055
It's not a huge clutter.

84
00:04:35,636 --> 00:04:37,177
Communicate with visual literacy.

85
00:04:38,078 --> 00:04:40,100
So this is just good artwork.

86
00:04:40,140 --> 00:04:41,121
Don't just throw it up there.

87
00:04:41,221 --> 00:04:41,861
Think about it.

88
00:04:42,001 --> 00:04:42,722
Plan it out.

89
00:04:43,583 --> 00:04:44,504
Avoid overload.

90
00:04:45,605 --> 00:04:48,627
If you fill everything with tremendous detail, people are

91
00:04:48,647 --> 00:04:49,348
going to get tired.

92
00:04:50,009 --> 00:04:52,411
You can't look at everything and focus on every detail.

93
00:04:53,231 --> 00:04:53,932
Be sparing.

94
00:04:54,653 --> 00:04:55,994
Choose important visuals.

95
00:04:58,030 --> 00:05:00,713
This is a very important one. Tell one story at a time.

96
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:05,777
So, again as I said, at Imagineering it all begins with a story.

97
00:05:06,557 --> 00:05:09,820
So everything in a land has to make sense.

98
00:05:11,241 --> 00:05:18,427
You know, you wouldn't have Fantasyland and place NASCAR Days of Thunder racing simulator in it.

99
00:05:19,068 --> 00:05:23,371
You'd be telling two different stories, the two stories don't match, the guests feel that.

100
00:05:24,645 --> 00:05:25,826
and they know something's wrong.

101
00:05:25,946 --> 00:05:27,868
So your storytelling needs to make sense.

102
00:05:28,809 --> 00:05:29,850
Avoid contradiction.

103
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:32,092
It's very similar to the last point.

104
00:05:33,113 --> 00:05:35,234
Now for every ounce of treatment, provide a ton of fun.

105
00:05:36,796 --> 00:05:38,177
This is sweat the details.

106
00:05:39,458 --> 00:05:43,782
This means it's not just good enough to tell a clear story.

107
00:05:44,242 --> 00:05:46,584
You wanna give them as much value as possible.

108
00:05:46,964 --> 00:05:49,426
And that really is baked into Imagineering,

109
00:05:49,847 --> 00:05:53,230
back from the original Imagineers, as told by Walt Disney.

110
00:05:53,893 --> 00:05:54,513
and keep it up.

